      "side": 1,
      "message": "Apart from the positive and negative cases in the scripts/generate_auth_certificates.py, I flashed this code to a real BMC and ran my client (which was actually the one revealed problem) in different modes. It\u0027s in rust, it uses 2 TLS backends - nativessl (openssl) that has session resumption disabled and rustls that has session resumption enabled. So I tested this using 4 permutations:\n1. forced http1 \u0026\u0026 nativtls - session resumption disabled\n2. forced http1 \u0026\u0026 rustls - session resumption enabled\n3. not forced http1 (upgraded to http2) \u0026\u0026 nativtls - session resumption disabled\n4. not forced http1 (upgraded to http2) \u0026\u0026 rustls - session resumption enabled\n\nWhen I was running tests I had `journalctl -f bmcweb | grep TLS` running to make sure resumption is working, so I had these (show for 2 runs only):\n```\nMar 18 03:12:16 \u003chostname redacted\u003e bmcweb[560]: [http_connection.hpp:249] 0x1c4ee18 Establishing mTLS session after handshake, session reused: false\nMar 18 03:15:04 \u003chostname redacted\u003e bmcweb[560]: [http_connection.hpp:249] 0x14433d0 Establishing mTLS session after handshake, session reused: false\n\nMar 18 03:20:20 \u003chostname redacted\u003e bmcweb[560]: [http_connection.hpp:249] 0x14433d0 Establishing mTLS session after handshake, session reused: false\nMar 18 03:20:25 \u003chostname redacted\u003e bmcweb[560]: [http_connection.hpp:249] 0x141f330 Establishing mTLS session after handshake, session reused: true\n```\n\nThis is a test client that pulls various info from BMC - logs, sensors, Firmwares and Chassis object, etc. It makes more than a dozen requests as part of one session, some of them concurrently. All the operations succeeded.",
