      },
      "lineNbr": 169,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-18T11:50:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "constructX509 is not quite re-usable here:\n1. It\u0027s a static and is not exposed in hpp file.\n2. It generates a key+cert bundle as a string, here we need just X509, if the test reuses the function, the string will need to be parsed.\n3. constructX509 generates production cert with particular extensions and properties (country, org). So constructX509 is a \"give me a complete cert file\" function. MtlsHandshake needs fine-grained control to set up specific test scenarios (null certs, missing extensions, etc.).",
      "parentUuid": "eb4870e8_740f9222",
      "revId": "98baa47753d53cd035b7b35c11629233b5e84df6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f0d97868_ffdf395e",
        "filename": "test/http/mutual_tls.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 169,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000153
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-18T22:17:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. Is trivially fixable without rewriting code\n2. Why is parsing a problem?  This is a unit test.  Functionally it will be a lot less duplicated code.\n3. Can we just pass in an argument for these things?\n\n\nI\u0027d really like to avoid the duplication that is here between all the tests that generate x509.  I\u0027m not qualified to review this much openssl code.",
      "parentUuid": "462d4e46_79de790e",
      "revId": "98baa47753d53cd035b7b35c11629233b5e84df6",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
